Parsing Eye Events from Eye Samples using a Velocity Based Algorithm

Here we will look at a Eye Events Parser. This is not a suggested parser, or the best parser, infact it may be a crappy parser. More testing from different eye trackers and data sets is needed before anything can be said about how well the following approach works.

The example code is useful from the point of view of showing how one might go about trying to develop a parsing algorithm in python, including at least some of the steps that may be taken during such a research project.

Notes:

  • Will handle monocular data.
  • Use a Velocity / Accelleration based Parsing Model.
  • Filter data streams as needed.

  • Use some heuristics to identify possible false alarms

    • Maximum Realistic Velocity and Accelleration values
    • Peak Velocity Point within Saccade Candidates
    • Minimum / Maximum Event Durations
    • Others ??

  • Focus on creating an off-line parser. An on-line version can be homework. ;)

II. Create Various Flavours of the Data Streams to be Used, Handling Missing Data Gaps

# Process sample streams
#

BINOC_EYE=0
SPATIAL_FILTER_WINDOW_SIZE=5
VELOCITY_FILTER_WINDOW_SIZE=5
PLOT_SIZE=19,11

gaze_field_groups=ET_WORKBOOK_INFO['gaze_fields']
pupil_size_fields=ET_WORKBOOK_INFO['pupil_size_fields']

def createTrialDataStreams():
    trial_data_streams=[]
    for t,trial_data in enumerate(multi_trial_sample_data):
        #Create a mask to be used to define periods of missing data in a data trace (eye tracker dependent)
        invalid_data_masks=[]
        if EYE_TRACKER_USED=='SRR':
            invalid_data_masks.append(trial_data.pupil_measure1==0)
            
        elif EYE_TRACKER_USED=='TOBII':
            invalid_data_masks.append(trial_data.status//10>=2)
            invalid_data_masks.append(trial_data.status%10>=2)
    
        time=trial_data.time
        pupil=getattr(trial_data,pupil_size_fields[BINOC_EYE])
        
        # Get x, y eye position traces (in pixels), setting sample positions where there is track loss
        # to NaN.
        xpix_cleared=getattr(trial_data,gaze_field_groups[BINOC_EYE][0]).copy()
        ypix_cleared=getattr(trial_data,gaze_field_groups[BINOC_EYE][1]).copy()
        processSampleEventGaps(xpix_cleared,ypix_cleared,pupil,invalid_data_masks[BINOC_EYE],'clear')
    
        # Get x, y eye position traces (in pixels), setting sample positions where there is track loss
        # to be linearly interpolated using each missing_sample_start-1 and missing_sample_end+1 as the points to
        # interpolate between.
        xpix_linear=getattr(trial_data,gaze_field_groups[BINOC_EYE][0]).copy()
        ypix_linear=getattr(trial_data,gaze_field_groups[BINOC_EYE][1]).copy()
    
        # valid_data_periods is a list of array slice objects giving the start,end index of each non missing 
        # period of in the data stream.
        valid_data_periods=processSampleEventGaps(xpix_linear,ypix_linear,pupil,invalid_data_masks[BINOC_EYE],'linear')
     
        # Convert from pixels to visual angle coordinates
        calibration_area_info=ET_WORKBOOK_INFO['calibration_area_info']
        vac=VisualAngleCalc(**calibration_area_info)      
        xdeg,ydeg=vac.pix2deg(xpix_linear,ypix_linear)
    
        # Create Filtered versions of the x and y degree data traces
        # We'll try using the Median Filter...
        xdeg_filtered = scipy.signal.medfilt(xdeg,SPATIAL_FILTER_WINDOW_SIZE)
        ydeg_filtered = scipy.signal.medfilt(ydeg,SPATIAL_FILTER_WINDOW_SIZE)
        
        # Create the velocity stream
        xvel=calculateVelocity(time,xdeg_filtered)
        yvel=calculateVelocity(time,ydeg_filtered)

        FILTER_ORDER=2
        Wn=0.3#((ET_SAMPLING_HZ/2.0)*(NYQUIST_FREQ_PERC*0.01))/ET_SAMPLING_HZ
        b, a = scipy.signal.butter(FILTER_ORDER, Wn, 'low')
        ffunc=scipy.signal.filtfilt
        xvel_filtered = ffunc(b, a, xvel)
        yvel_filtered = ffunc(b, a, yvel)

#        xvel_filtered=savitzky_golay(xvel,window_size=VELOCITY_FILTER_WINDOW_SIZE,order=2)
#        yvel_filtered=savitzky_golay(yvel,window_size=VELOCITY_FILTER_WINDOW_SIZE,order=2)
#        xvel_filtered=gaussian_filter1d(xvel,VELOCITY_FILTER_WINDOW_SIZE)
#        yvel_filtered=gaussian_filter1d(yvel,VELOCITY_FILTER_WINDOW_SIZE)
#        xvel_filtered=scipy.signal.medfilt(xvel,VELOCITY_FILTER_WINDOW_SIZE)
#        yvel_filtered=scipy.signal.medfilt(yvel,VELOCITY_FILTER_WINDOW_SIZE)

        velocity=np.sqrt(xvel*xvel+yvel*yvel)
        #velocity_filtered=xvel_filtered=savitzky_golay(velocity,window_size=VELOCITY_FILTER_WINDOW_SIZE,order=2)
        velocity_filtered=np.sqrt(xvel_filtered*xvel_filtered+yvel_filtered*yvel_filtered)
    
        # Create the accelleration stream
        xacc=calculateAccelleration(time,xdeg_filtered)
        yacc=calculateAccelleration(time,ydeg_filtered)
        accelleration=np.sqrt(xacc*xacc+yacc*yacc)
    
        # Create a data trace dictionary for all the different types
        #  of data traces created for the trial
        #
        trial_data={}
        trial_data['time']=time
        trial_data['xpix_cleared']=xpix_cleared
        trial_data['ypix_cleared']=ypix_cleared
        trial_data['xpix_linear']=xpix_linear
        trial_data['xpix_linear']=xpix_linear
        trial_data['xdeg']=xdeg
        trial_data['ydeg']=ydeg
        trial_data['xdeg_filtered']=xdeg_filtered
        trial_data['ydeg_filtered']=ydeg_filtered
        trial_data['pupil']=pupil
        trial_data['velocity']=velocity
        trial_data['velocity_filtered']=velocity_filtered
        trial_data['accelleration']=accelleration
        trial_data['valid_data_periods']=valid_data_periods
        trial_data['missing_data_mask']=invalid_data_masks[BINOC_EYE]
        # Add the data trace dictionary to a list
        #
        trial_data_streams.append(trial_data)
    return trial_data_streams

def calculateVelocityThresholdPerTrial(trial_data_streams):
    for t,trial_data in enumerate(trial_data_streams):
#        display("Trial {0}: vel min={1}, max={2}, avg={3}, median={4} std={5}".format(
#                        t+1,
#                        valid_velocity_filtered.min(),
#                        valid_velocity_filtered.max(),
#                        valid_velocity_filtered.mean(),
#                        np.median(valid_velocity_filtered),
#                        valid_velocity_filtered.std())) 
        
        pt_list=[]        
        missing_data_mask=trial_data['missing_data_mask']
        valid_velocity_filtered=trial_data['velocity_filtered'][~missing_data_mask[1:-1]]
        PT=valid_velocity_filtered.min()+np.array(valid_velocity_filtered,dtype=float64).std()*3.0
        velocity_below_thresh=valid_velocity_filtered[valid_velocity_filtered<PT]
        PTd=2.0
        while PTd >= 1.0:   
            if len(pt_list)>0:
                PT=velocity_below_thresh.mean()+3.0*np.array(velocity_below_thresh,dtype=float64).std()
                velocity_below_thresh=valid_velocity_filtered[valid_velocity_filtered<PT]
                PTd=np.abs(PT-pt_list[-1])
#            display("valid_velocity_filtered: PTd {},PT {}, sample count {}, min {}, max {}, mean {}, std {}".format(PTd,PT,velocity_below_thresh.shape,
#                                                               velocity_below_thresh.min(),
#                                                               velocity_below_thresh.max(),
#                                                               velocity_below_thresh.mean(),
#                                                               velocity_below_thresh.std()))
            pt_list.append(PT)
#        display(pt_list)
        saccade_candidate_mask=(valid_velocity_filtered>=PT)
        saccade_candidate_periods=np.ma.extras.notmasked_contiguous(
                                np.ma.array(valid_velocity_filtered,
                                            mask=saccade_candidate_mask)
                                )                                
#        display('--------')
        trial_data['velocity_threshold_points']=np.asarray(pt_list)
        trial_data['saccade_candidate_mask']=saccade_candidate_mask
        trial_data['saccade_candidate_periods']=saccade_candidate_periods

#        display('Trial : %d'%t)
#        display('PT count : %d'%len(pt_list))
#        display('points : {}'.format(pt_list))
#        display('PT1 : %f'%pt_list[0])
#        display('PTe : %f'%pt_list[-1])
#        display('PTdv : %f'%(np.abs(pt_list[-1]-pt_list[-2])))
#        display('--------')
        
trial_data_streams=createTrialDataStreams()
calculateVelocityThresholdPerTrial(trial_data_streams)

Plot the Traces Created

plt.rcParams['figure.figsize']=PLOT_SIZE


deg_pos_colors=((0.,.25,0.),(0.,.75,0.),(0.,0.,.25),(0.,0.,.25),(0.,0.,0.))
velocity_colors=((.25,0.,0.),(.75,0.,0.),(.5,0.,0.))

for t,trial_traces_dict in enumerate(trial_data_streams):
    time=trial_traces_dict['time']
    pupil=trial_traces_dict['pupil']
    xdeg=trial_traces_dict['xdeg']
    ydeg=trial_traces_dict['ydeg']
    xdeg_filtered=trial_traces_dict['xdeg_filtered']
    ydeg_filtered=trial_traces_dict['ydeg_filtered']
    velocity=trial_traces_dict['velocity']
    velocity_filtered=trial_traces_dict['velocity_filtered']
    missing_data_mask=trial_traces_dict['missing_data_mask']
    
    fig = plt.figure()
    fig.title=("Trial %d Eye Data Strip Chart"%(t+1))

    ax=plt.gca()
#    ax.plot(time,xdeg,label='Horz. Pos. (Degrees)',color=deg_pos_colors[0])
#    ax.plot(time,ydeg,label='Vert. Pos. (Degrees)',color=deg_pos_colors[2])
    xdeg_filtered[missing_data_mask]=np.NaN
    ydeg_filtered[missing_data_mask]=np.NaN
    ax.plot(time,xdeg_filtered,label='Filtered Horz. Pos. (Degrees)',color=deg_pos_colors[1])
    ax.plot(time,ydeg_filtered,label='Filtered Vert. Pos. (Degrees)',color=deg_pos_colors[3])

    tmin=time.min()//1
    tmax=time.max()//1+1
    plt.xticks(np.arange(tmin,tmax,0.5),rotation='vertical')
    trans = mtransforms.blended_transform_factory(ax.transData, ax.transAxes)
    ax.fill_between(time, 0, 1, where=pupil==0, facecolor=(.2,.2,.2), alpha=0.5, transform=trans)


    ax.fill_between(time[1:-1], 0, 1, where=trial_traces_dict['velocity_filtered']>=trial_traces_dict['velocity_threshold_points'][-1],facecolor=(.5,0,.5), alpha=0.5, transform=trans)

    ax.set_xlabel('Time')
    ax.set_ylabel('Position (Degrees)',color=deg_pos_colors[-1])
    for tl in ax.get_yticklabels():
        tl.set_color(deg_pos_colors[-1])
    
    ax2 = ax.twinx()
#    ax2.plot(time[1:-1],velocity,label='XY Velocity',color=velocity_colors[0])
    ax2.plot(time[1:-1],velocity_filtered,label='Filtered XY Velocity',color=velocity_colors[1])
    ax2.set_ylabel('Velocity (degrees / second)',color=velocity_colors[-1])
    for tl in ax2.get_yticklabels():
        tl.set_color(velocity_colors[-1])

    plt.axhline(y=trial_traces_dict['velocity_threshold_points'][0],color='g')
    plt.axhline(y=trial_traces_dict['velocity_threshold_points'][-1],color='r')

    handles, labels = ax.get_legend_handles_labels()
    handles2, labels2 = ax2.get_legend_handles_labels()
    handles.extend(handles2)
    labels.extend(labels2)
    legend(handles,labels,bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc=2, borderaxespad=0.) #plt.legend(loc=(1.01,.8))        

    plt.grid()
    plt.show()
